[1691.212703, "i", "XY: 12x12 (bowls contain ball)\n# Total: 12x12x12 = 1728 (worse)\n\n# Ball z=0..5, bowls z=4..9 (overlap z=4,5)\n# At z=4,5: ball and bowls must not share XY\n# Ball XY at z=4,5: full circle (56 cells)\n# Bowls XY: 90 cells (nested)\n# 56+90 = 146 > 144 (12x12) -> can't fit in 12x12!\n# Need at least 13x12 or 12x13 -> 13x13x10 = 1690 (worse)\n\n# What about ball z=0..5, 3 bowls z=0..5 (same z, no XY overlap)\n# + 2 bowls z=6..11\n# 3 bowls nested: 12x8x6 (with ball)\n# 2 bowls at z=6..11: 12x6x6\n# Combined: 12x max(8+ball,6) x 12\n# Ball+3bowls: 12x14x6 (ball y=0..7, bowls y=6,8,10)\n# 2 bowls at z=6: 12x6x6 at y=0..5\n# Total: 12x14x12 = 2016 (worse)\n\n# I'm convinced 1368 is hard to beat. Let me check one more thing:\n# What if I use 12x18x6 with a different bowl nesting that creates\n# an 8-wide gap?\n\n# Bowl XY:\n# y=0: ##........##  (x=0,1,10,11)\n# y=1: .##......##.  (x=1,2,9,10)\n# y=2: ..##....##..  (x=2,3,8,9)\n# y=3: ...######...  (x=3,4,5,6,7,8)\n\n# Interior at y=0: x=2..9 (8 cells!) \n# If I could place donut1 at the bowl "]
