[1691.212722, "i", "interior y=0 row...\n# But the ball occupies x=0..9 at y=6 (ball's y=6: x=2..7)\n# And bowl1 at y=6 has y=0 row at y=6: x=0,1,10,11\n# So at y=6: ball has x=2..7, bowl has x=0,1,10,11\n# Empty at y=6: x=8,9 only (2 cells)\n\n# What if I shift the ball in x? Ball at x=4..13?\n# Then at y=6: ball has x=6..11, bowl has x=0,1,10,11\n# Overlap at x=10,11! Can't do that.\n\n# Ball at x=2..11: at y=6, ball has x=4..9, bowl has x=0,1,10,11\n# No overlap! And at y=6, empty: x=2,3 (from ball gap)\n# Hmm, still not 8 contiguous.\n\nprint(\"Current solution: 12x19x6 = 1368\")\nprint(\"This appears to be near-optimal for this object set.\")\nprint(\"The bottleneck is donut1 (8x4x1) which needs 8 contiguous units.\")\nEOF\n"]
